Boinc
From iA wiki
BOINC [1] is an acronym for Berkeley Open Infrastructure for Network Computing and generalizes the original SETI@Home concept of distributed computing to allow support for multiple projects. Installing a boinc client allows a user to attach to various projects and to determine what percentage of computing time to devote to which projects.
